review_blob: Had on tap, aroma is pleasant, typical of a Belgian Abbey Ale, surprisingly smooth, was excellent cold and didnt need time to warm up.  Dry finish, quite enjoyable.

Surprised by this; didnt care for many apricot wheats before.  Good aroma;  taste is great; had both bottle and tap.  Very smooth and creamy, like the old Celis White had been.  Leaves you wanting a lot more.
